<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-09-29T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-09-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/391: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-29T10:00:00-03:00">September
                                    29, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 29—9:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reliably reported that <persName corresp="#p_KGB1">General
                                Klinger</persName> telegraphed last night to Rio de Janeiro asking
                            for armistice but that field commanders do not agree.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Embassy at Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>